The <b>Orange-billed Sparrow</b> (<i>Arremon aurantiirostris</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird" title="Bird">bird</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emberizidae" title="Emberizidae">Emberizidae</a> family. In <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_America" title="Central America">Central America</a> it is found in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belize" title="Belize">Belize</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Costa_Rica" title="Costa Rica">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guatemala" title="Guatemala">Guatemala</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Honduras" title="Honduras">Honduras</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicaragua" title="Nicaragua">Nicaragua</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Panama" title="Panama">Panama</a>. In northeastern <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_America" title="South America">South America</a> the Orange-billed Sparrow is found in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colombia" title="Colombia">Colombia</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecuador" title="Ecuador">Ecuador</a> and northern <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peru" title="Peru">Peru</a>. The species are <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black" title="Black">black</a> coloured, and as a name suggests, have an <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orange_(colour)" title="Orange (colour)">orange</a> bill.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitat</a> is subtropical or tropical moist lowland <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forest" title="Forest">forests</a>.
